# Acquisition Portfolio by Agency Type

Understanding which acquisition channels and strategies work best for different agency types, service models, and client segments.

## Core Principle

**Not all acquisition channels work equally well for all agencies.**

- Channel effectiveness depends on:
  - Service type
  - Deal size
  - Sales cycle length
  - ICP characteristics
  - Geographic focus
  - Competitive positioning

**This guide maps optimal acquisition portfolios by agency type.**

---

## The Acquisition Channel Universe

### Inbound Marketing Channels

**SEO / Organic Content:**
- Time to results: 6-18 months
- Cost: Medium (content creation + technical)
- Scalability: High (compounds over time)
- Best for: Ongoing need, research-heavy buyers

**Paid Search (Google Ads):**
- Time to results: 1-3 months
- Cost: High (CPC competitive)
- Scalability: Medium (limited by budget and keywords)
- Best for: High-intent, immediate need

**Social Media (Organic):**
- Time to results: 3-12 months
- Cost: Low-Medium (time intensive)
- Scalability: Medium (platform dependent)
- Best for: Brand building, thought leadership

**Social Media (Paid):**
- Time to results: 1-3 months
- Cost: Medium (varies by platform)
- Scalability: High (easy to scale budget)
- Best for: Specific targeting, retargeting

**Content Marketing / Thought Leadership:**
- Time to results: 6-24 months
- Cost: Medium (creation + distribution)
- Scalability: High (compounds)
- Best for: Complex sales, long cycles

---

### Outbound Sales Channels

**Email Outreach:**
- Time to results: 1-3 months
- Cost: Low-Medium (tools + time)
- Scalability: High (automation)
- Best for: Defined ICP, volume approach

**LinkedIn Outreach:**
- Time to results: 1-3 months
- Cost: Low (time intensive)
- Scalability: Medium (limited by platform rules)
- Best for: B2B, executive buyers

**Cold Calling:**
- Time to results: 1-2 months
- Cost: High (dedicated sales resource)
- Scalability: Low (time intensive, doesn't scale easily)
- Best for: Large deals, complex sales

**Account-Based Marketing (ABM):**
- Time to results: 3-9 months
- Cost: High (highly customized)
- Scalability: Low (manual, targeted)
- Best for: Enterprise accounts, strategic targets

---

### Partnership / Network Channels

**Referrals:**
- Time to results: Ongoing
- Cost: Very low (relationship maintenance)
- Scalability: Low (network limited)
- Best for: All agency types (universal)

**Strategic Partnerships:**
- Time to results: 3-12 months (setup + ramp)
- Cost: Medium (time + revenue share)
- Scalability: Medium (limited by partner capacity)
- Best for: Complementary services, channel expansion

**Platform Partnerships:**
- Time to results: 6-18 months
- Cost: Medium-High (certification, training, co-marketing)
- Scalability: High (if partner grows)
- Best for: Technology-focused agencies

**Reseller Relationships:**
- Time to results: 3-9 months
- Cost: Medium (setup + commission structure)
- Scalability: High (leveraging others' sales teams)
- Best for: Productized services, repeatable offerings

---

### Event / Community Channels

**Speaking / Conferences:**
- Time to results: 3-12 months
- Cost: Medium (travel + time)
- Scalability: Low (founder-dependent)
- Best for: Thought leadership positioning

**Webinars / Virtual Events:**
- Time to results: 1-6 months
- Cost: Low-Medium
- Scalability: High (repeatable)
- Best for: Education-based marketing

**Community Building:**
- Time to results: 12-36 months
- Cost: Medium (platform + moderation)
- Scalability: Medium (engagement intensive)
- Best for: Long-term brand building

**Sponsorships:**
- Time to results: 3-12 months
- Cost: High (sponsorship fees)
- Scalability: Medium (budget dependent)
- Best for: Brand visibility, specific audiences

